Submitting a Change Request:A request for a change that is more than a simple Technical Correction to one of HL7's specifications.
<script type="text/javascript">
if (document.getElementById('stepped-process') != null) {
AJS.$('div.aui-message').css('display', 'none');
}
</script>





Duplicate:The resolution of the target issue will be treated as the resolution of this issue.  All watchers and "in person" requests will be copied from this issue to the target issue.
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.$('div.comment-input').css('display', 'none');
if (document.getElementById('stepped-process') != null) {
AJS.$('div.aui-message').css('display', 'none');
}
</script>





Affirmative Vote:By voting a feedback item as "Affirmative":
<ul>
<li>You are asserting that, while you would like the item addressed, you are comfortable with the specification proceeding to publication if this item is not addressed immediately or as requested.</li>
<li>You understand this will cause your overall vote on the specification to be set to "Affirmative" unless you have made (or do make) negative comments.  If your vote was previously set to be the "same as" another voter, that link will be removed.</li>
</ul>
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.$('div.comment-input').css('display', 'none');
if (document.getElementById('stepped-process') != null) {
AJS.$('div.aui-message').css('display', 'none');
}
</script>





Voting Negative:By voting a feedback item as "Negative":
<ul>
<li>You are asserting that you do not believe the specification should proceed to publication until this issue is fixed</li>
<li>You understand this will cause your overall vote on the specification to be set to "Negative".  If your vote was previously set to be the "same as" another voter, that link will be removed.</li>
</ul>
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.$('div.comment-input').css('display', 'none');
if (document.getElementById('stepped-process') != null) {
AJS.$('div.aui-message').css('display', 'none');
}
</script>





Remove Vote:By removing this vote item, it will no longer count as part of your overall ballot submission.  It will be deleted with no record of it included as part of your ballot.  
<br/>
If this item vote is the only remaining negative ballot vote for the submission, the submission's overall vote will change to affirmative.
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.$('div.comment-input').css('display', 'none');
if (document.getElementById('stepped-process') != null) {
AJS.$('div.aui-message').css('display', 'none');
}
</script>





Retract Vote:By retracting this vote item, you are indicating that, based on your new understanding, the feedback item is no longer (or never was) an issue.<br/>
The ballot vote will no longer count as part of your overall ballot submission.  
<br/>
If this item vote is the only remaining negative ballot vote for the submission, the submission's overall vote will change to affirmative.
